e,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65222","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65222"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBiliary tract neoplasms can present with various signs and symptoms which are often related to interference with bile flow.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common mode of presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased alkaline phosphatase","Decreased conjugated bilirubin","Decreased gamma-glutamyl transferase","Obstructive jaundice","Right upper quadrant pain and fever"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EBiliary tract neoplasms typically cause obstruction of bile flow, leading to:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EObstructive jaundice \u003C/strong\u003Eis the classic presentation due to blockage of bile ducts. There will be elevation of conjugated bilirubin, alkaline phosphatase and the transaminases\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased alkaline phosphatase\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - levels are typically elevated due to biliary obstruction\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased conjugated bilirubin\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - levels increase due to impaired bile flow\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight upper quadrant pain and fever\u003C/strong\u003E could be consistent with cholangitis, but cholangitis is more often due to stone, inflammation or infection - and occasionally, neoplasms\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased gamma-glutamyl transferase\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - levels typically increase with biliary obstruction\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe obstruction leads to backing up of bile, causing jaundice, pruritus, and an increased risk of ascending cholangitis. Laboratory tests typically show elevated liver enzymes, particularly alkaline phosphatase and gamma-glutamyl transferase.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Biliary tract neoplasms typically present with obstructive jaundice, right upper quadrant pain, and elevated alkaline phosphatase.","Cholangitis is a common complication of biliary obstruction from neoplasms."],"references":["Zamani Z, Fatima S. Biliary Tract Cancer. 2023 Jul 10. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809385.","Gore RM, Shelhamer RP. Biliary tract neoplasms: diagnosis and staging. Cancer Imaging. 2007 Oct 1;7 Spec No A(Special issue A):S15-23. doi: 10.1102/1470-7330.2007.9016. PMID: 17921093; PMCID: PMC2727973.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50659"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15217"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50659","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50659"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-25T21:31:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-25T21:32:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7908"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65222"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHe